WITH regard to the text of the Germania of Tacitus in this edition, a very few words will be enough. Although not exactly corresponding with any other, as far as I know, the text nearly represents that of Massmann (Quedlingburg and Leipsig, 1847), from which it only differs in a few places, where I think the other readings adopted have better manuscript authority, or are intrinsically more probable.
